The paper deals with the problem of learning the structure of a Markov random field, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The specific type of Markov random field studied is the $H$-coloring, which is a combinatorial structure on graphs, making it relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses connections to statistical physics, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions computational complexity results, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.CC).
